Also, with Homecoming being moved, we will not be having an early release on Friday, September 25th.

shared_text:
VCSC News
April 9 at 1:56 PM ¬∑

Good morning all,

I certainly know that many of you are dealing with larger issues this morning from the storm. It is an E-Learning or counted day for education in the VCSC but this is secondary and quite frankly if it does not occur today, it does not occur.

Many of you are without power and this includes many of our staff members as well and they simply may not be available during the hours of 9AM to 2PM.

As we have learned with Covid-19, we have to be flexible. We just did not know that today that Covid-19 would become secondary for many of us and our attention would turn elsewhere and with this we must be flexible today and patient as we have too many people dealing with much larger issues than that of education and this is primarily related to the storm from last night.

Hopefully we will slowly start to return to what is the new normal for the time being, but today, education is far more secondary.

Hope you all are safe and with this, please stay safe!

Mr. Parsley

post_text: Tomorrow, we are distributing food from 9 a.m.-11 a.m. at Tecumseh, Riley, Washington School, Vigo and Lincoln. We are trying to do this in the safest way possible. Please open trunks or hatches on vehicles (then stand at least six feet away) so we don't have to make direct contact. Also, if you are on the delivery list, please do not also go pick up at a school. If you are able to pick up, please let us know so that we can give your delivery spot to someone who really needs it. Lastly, we are packing products to the best of our ability while dealing with delivery and product availability restraints. We do not have the means to customize meals based on a child's likes and dislikes. Thank you. Sodexo and Franklin

VCSC Kindergarten Registration is HERE, with an early online option!

On Tuesday, March 10th from 4pm-6:30pm all VCSC elementary schools will be hosting kindergarten registration.

To register your child, please go to the school district that your child lives in. Yes, you will still need to go to the school on registration day EVEN IF YOU FILL OUT THE INFORMATION ONLINE.

To find what district you live in, please click on the link and enter your address.

Find my district: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-elementary-school-distric/home?fbclid=IwAR1vxmvX0_U75chcMjES5ho_Qxtymd0prqP3XL4ywdVCj9l7UeFmd5YcmRc

Please bring your child‚Äôs birth certificate, immunization records, and proof of address.

Your child must be 5 years old by August 1, 2020.

Online Kindergarten Registration: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-kg-reg-2033/home

We can‚Äôt wait to see you!

post_text:
Agenda for Kindergarten Registration March 10th 4:00-6:30 p.m.
Melissa Pancake, Principal

***Enter back doors of Washington School***

*Meet registration staff as they greet and place a name tag on your child. Parent receives registration folder to complete. (Gymnasium)

*Child is escorted by our staff to complete kindergarten readiness screening.

*Parents hand birth certificates and immunization records to staff for copying.

*Parents show proof of address to staff member to verify child resides within Franklin boundaries.

*Parents meet the kindergarten teachers and hear a presentation at one of the following times: 4:15 p.m., 5:00 p.m., or 5:45 p.m. (Mrs. Bahr's classroom)

*Child is returned to parent after screenings are completed. (Gymnasium)

*Parents get a copy of the screening results before checkout. (Gymnasium)

*Parent and child go to the checkout table to turn in all paperwork, take future Viking photo and receive a VCSC registration goody bag. (Gymnasium)

Thank you for attending our 2020 Kindergarten Registration. We look forward to serving the class of 2033.
